Tenants at an apartment on the upper level of an outbuilding in Sunford were fortunately not at home when a fire ripped through the building causing extensive damage on Monday night.
The Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) Phoenix Operations Centre received multiple calls from residents of Cotford Place in Sunford at approximately 22:55 reporting an explosion.
RUSA boss, Prem Balram, said: “On arrival, Reaction Officers found firefighters from the Ethekwini Fire Department extinguishing the blaze that rapidly spread through an upper level apartment of an outbuilding. The cause of the fire or explosion was not determined.
Thankfully, the tenants who occupy the flat were not at home at the time of the incident. The blaze was contained and extinguished through the efforts of firefighters.”
Investigations are underway.